df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(goals, orient='index', columns=['Goals'])
    df.index = df.index.map(lambda x: f"Team {x}")

    df['Penalties'] = pd.Series(penalties)
    df.index = df.index.map(lambda x: f"Team {x}")

    df.reset_index(inplace=True)

    df['Goals'] = df['Goals'].astype(float)
    df['Penalties'] = df['Penalties'].astype(float)

    df = df[['Team', 'Goals', 'Penalties']]

    plot = sns.pairplot(
        data=df,
        diag_kind='kde',
        plot_kws=dict(alpha=0.5),
        size=15
    )

    return df, plot

# Create a dictionary mapping the goals and penalties to their corresponding team names
    goal_dict = {team: goals[team] for team in goals}
    penalty_dict = {team: penalties[team] for team in penalties}

    # Create a dataframe from the goal_dict and penalty_dict
    df = pd.DataFrame(list(zip(goal_dict.keys(), goal_dict.values(), penalty_dict.values())))
    df.columns = ['Team', 'Goals', 'Penalties']

    # Create a seaborn pairplot with the goals and penalties column
    sns.pairplot(df, hue='Team', palette='husl')
    return df, plot

# Create a DataFrame using the input data
    df = pd.DataFrame({

    # Visualize the goals and penalties distribution using a pairplot
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, figsize=(8, 8))
    sns.pairplot(df, hue='Team', y_vars='Goals', x_vars='Penalties', ax=axes[0])
    sns.pairplot(df, hue='Team', y_vars='Penalties', x_vars='Goals', ax=axes[1])
    return df, fig

# Convert dictionaries into DataFrames
    goals_df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(goals, orient="index", columns=["Goals"])

    df = goals_df.join(penalties_df, lsuffix="_Goals", rsuffix="_Penalties")

    df.pop('Penalties_Goals')

    return df, plot

    df_goals = pd.DataFrame({'Team': goals.keys(), 'Goals': goals.values()})

    return df, axes
